data.title: Amazon Accelerate 2024
data.text:
Angela Anderson is a Senior Business Development Manager at Amazon, where she overseas enterprise sales for the brand protection program Transparency. Angela has worked at Amazon for 12 years and in 2012 was one of the first Strategic Account Managers focused on helping 3P Sellers grow their business on Amazon. She also led the first-ever Seller conference in 2015. She is passionate about listening to brands and working closely with them to solve their challenges. Born and raised in Seattle, she now lives in the Silverdale area with her fiancée and French Bulldog.

Chris Anderson is a Senior Product Manager at Amazon focused on building tools that allow selling partners to easily manage their 3D content. Chris brings his passion for photography to Amazon where has been instrumental in delivering new visual content management tools that improve the selling partner experience. Based in Seattle, Chris spends much of his free time exploring the mountains of the Pacific Northwest.

Louis Andres is a Senior Technical Product Manager for Amazon's Selling Partner Experience team. In his current role, Louis primarily builds experiences for selling partners that use generative artificial intelligence (AI) to streamline product listings and enhance customer-facing detail pages. After earning his MBA from UCLA Anderson, Louis joined the Amazon and led multiple programs that improved seller error resolution and created higher quality listings. Prior to business school, he worked at Dell Technologies as a strategy analyst, product owner, and performance engineer. Outside of work, Louis is passionate about live music, tech gadgets, fitness tracking, and cheering on his hometown Dallas sports teams.

Based at Amazon’s Seattle headquarters, Natalie Angelillo leads a global team dedicated to showcasing how Amazon empowers sellers to grow their businesses. Before Amazon, Natalie was VP, Community & Communications at OfferUp, where she spearheaded PR, social, and community safety efforts, and built key relationships nationwide. She also founded and led several startups and held leadership roles at PhotoDisc/Getty Images, contributing to the reinvention of the $2B stock photography industry. Natalie holds a B.A. from UC Berkeley and an M.A. from the University of Washington.

Ali Babul is the Chief Evangelist at Trellis, leveraging a decade-spanning agency background to drive growth strategies for brands of all sizes. Possessing an acute awareness of immediate needs and overarching objectives, Ali specializes in orchestrating the expansion of products and the amplification of success for these brands. His pivotal role involves shedding light on the challenges that brands encounter while navigating diverse marketplaces.

Dr. Tom Bell is the Regulatory Engagement Manager within the Trustworthy Shopping Experience team at Amazon, overseeing the engagement strategy with EU and UK regulators. After earning his Doctorate in Chemistry from the University of Leicester in England, Tom has specialized in product safety for over a decade, including roles with the Consumer Group Which? and the UK product safety regulator, Office for Product Safety and Standards. Since joining Amazon nearly two years ago, he has led efforts to improve relationships with regulators, advocating to ensure new or revised regulations benefit both businesses and consumers. Based in London, Tom lives with his wife and daughter, and enjoys watching sports in his free time.

Tessa Blumenthal is the Senior Director of Operations at GO, a lifelong Washington resident, and an e-commerce professional with 12 years of experience specializing in shipping to Amazon. Drawing on her background as a former Amazon employee, she has extensive knowledge on how to avoid fines, reduce fees, and optimize your inbound shipping to fulfillment centers.

As a Senior Product Manager for Grade and Resell, Kylee Brown oversees the strategy for used Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA) products and returns. After graduating from the University of Washington, Kylee joined Amazon as a dispute analyst for wholesale liquidations. She then transitioned into product management, working in both customer return fraud and returns liquidation. With over seven years of experience, Kylee is committed to developing product strategies that create meaningful experiences for selling partners in our store. Originally from Seattle, she now lives in New York. When she's not working, you can find her reading or running marathons.

Kathryn Carlson is a Senior Product Manager for Worldwide Sustainability at Amazon, focusing on building sustainability solutions and services. After graduating from Seattle Pacific University, she joined Amazon where she's spent the last 11 years in roles across recruiting, trade-in, returns, physical stores, and AWS. She is a native of Kirkland, where she still lives today with her husband and miniature goldendoodle. Outside of work, she loves gardening and traveling, and serves on the board of the Bellevue Botanical Garden Society.

James Casazza is the Senior Manager of Product Management for the Selling Partner Experience Personalization team, overseeing Amazon's efforts to create delightful, personalized tools that supports the growth and success of selling partners in Amazon's store. Before joining Amazon in 2017, James earned a Master of Electrical and Computer Engineering from Carnegie Mellon University and an MBA from the University of Michigan. Since then, James led the redesign of the Seller Central homepage, transforming the page into a command center that provides selling partners with a summary of their performance and recommendations to support their success. With over 20 years of experience, James remains focused on creating valuable, meaningful experiences that help selling partners achieve their goals. Originally from New York, he now lives in Detroit with his wife and three sons. Outside of work, he enjoys running, soccer, and traveling to new places with his family.

Joy Chang is the Director of Selling Partner Support at Amazon, managing the product, technology, and editorial teams that power the features and tools selling partners use to contact support and resolve issues. Joy began her career in finance before earning her MBA from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania. Since joining Amazon 12 years ago, Joy has held a number of different roles focused on building customer experiences in our store. Last year, Joy transitioned to Selling Partner Services to improve the support experience for selling partners. She currently lives in Bellevue, Washington with her husband and two children. Outside of work, she enjoys cooking, creating art in different mediums, and running.

As a Tech Evangelist for Amazon Ads, Jeff Cohen travels the world sharing insights about our suite of advertising technologies. Since joining Amazon in 2022, Jeff has helped build an engaging and informative community within the Amazon Ads tech space, even building a weekly LinkedIn newsletter that's read by thousands of partners and advertisers. When Jeff is not pontificating about Amazon Ads, you can find him playing with his three kids, watching a Cardinals baseball game, or sipping on a glass of whiskey.

Sylvie Conti is a Senior Manager for Amazon's Selling Partner Trust organization, overseeing a product management team that owns the Account Health Rating and Account Health Assurance programs. Her team specifically focuses on providing selling partners with more transparency into their Account Health Rating, and works to identify and resolve issues that could potentially lead to account deactivation. Since joining Amazon, Sylvie has held a variety of roles that focus on supporting the growth of selling partners in our store, including small and black-owned businesses. Originally from Switzerland, she now lives in Seattle. When she's not working, Sylvie enjoys running, traveling, and eating delicious food with her husband and two daughters.

As a Senior Program Manager at Amazon, Lauren Coury leads the overall user experience within the A+ Content Manager. Since joining Amazon in 2019, Lauren has focused on improving the experience around Amazon's selling partner compliance policy. As part of the A+ Content program, Lauren has spearheaded the launch of Premium A+ Content on Seller Central, driven global expansion, and implemented automated improvements to help brands scale their A+ Content creation. Outside of work, she is a competitive runner who enjoys exploring the mountains.

Stephen has been the Chief Technology Officer at Jungle Scout since 2021, enhancing its platform for a new generation of Amazon sellers. Before joining Jungle Scout, he was the Director of Software Development at Amazon, overseeing programs like Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA) and technology teams for the dropshipping business. He helped launch over 120 seller features, introduced FBA in nine countries, and co-invented the patent for Seller Fulfilled Prime technology. Originally from Edmonton, Canada, he now lives in Seattle, WA.

Nadya Dhalla is the General Manager of Supply Chain by Amazon (SCA). SCA leverages Amazon’s assets, advanced technologies and supply chain capabilities that have been built over the past 20+ years to optimize a sellers’ end-to-end logistics, fulfillment, and transportation. While we are still in the beginning stages of SCA, the mission is to simplify all or part of the seller's supply chain decisions reliably, with greater visibility, at faster speeds and with lower costs, so sellers can continue innovating and building products that customers love. Nadya is a graduate of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, where she earned a Master's of Science degree in Engineering Systems and an MBA from the MIT Sloan School of Management.

Andrew DiSarno is an 8 year Amazonian and currently leads the Business Development and Account Management functions of the Western Region with Amazon Shipping. Andrew is one of the initial members of the US Amazon Shipping sales team and hired the US Business Development team in 2023 to launch Amazon Shipping. Prior to joining Amazon Shipping in late 2022, Andrew led the in-stock management, pricing, and vendor management functions of the Amazon subsidiary fabric.com.

Sarah DuBois is a Senior Manager at Amazon, overseeing the product direction for buyer abuse prevention. While Sarah has been an Amazonian for more than nine years, she’s spent more than six of those years within the world of abuse prevention working to safeguard brands, sellers, and buyers. She is passionate about keeping Amazon safe for customers and selling partners alike. Sarah lives in Seattle with her husband and two very active children.

Jorge Escalante is a Principal Marketing Manager at Amazon, leading go-to-market strategies for new products and initiatives that help Fulfilled by Merchant (FBM) selling partners succeed. He holds an Master of Science degree in Marketing from Johns Hopkins University and has over 10 years of experience in marketing, commercial, and digital strategy at P&G, CEMEX Research Group, and now, Amazon. Originally from Mexico and Spain, and having lived in over nine countries, Jorge has a diverse international background. He now resides in Seattle with his wife and two dogs.

Gabe Fishbein is the Vice President of Product Strategy at Flywheel Digital, overseeing the continuous delivery of first-to-market solutions that help brands improve and scale their ecommerce businesses. Since joining the company eight years ago, Gabe has focused on building Flywheel’s proprietary tech stack to address the unique needs and goals of selling partners in Amazon's store. Prior to joining Flywheel, Gabe co-built a successful business in Amazon's store as a selling partner. Gabe holds degrees from the University of Maryland in Information Systems and Marketing with a minor in Innovation and Entrepreneurship.

Gopal is the VP of Amazon's World Wide Returns and ReCommerce teams. Previously, he led the Amazon Distribution and Fulfillment Solutions business, including building a Warehouse Management System product to effectively manage distribution centers, and managing an eCommerce fulfillment business that helps organizations reach their consumers seamlessly for their DTC channels. He spent 5 years in as part of the founding team building the marketplace business in India. Gopal has an MBA from Kellogg School of Management and a BS in Computer Science and Engineering from University of Madras, India.

Marc Girdlestone is a Senior Product Manager at Veeqo, an Amazon company. For the past six years as a Product Manager, he has developed solutions that help ecommerce businesses streamline operations across channels like Amazon, Shopify, eBay, and Walmart. During this time, Marc spearheaded the launch of Veeqo's Digital Picking tool to improve warehouse picking accuracy and speed. He also played a key role in the release of Veeqo's US shipping product, which automatically selects the cheapest carrier rate meeting delivery promise. Originally from London, Marc is now based in Wales with his two children, and enjoys spending his free time helping them build Lego robots. He is passionate about optimizing multi-channel ecommerce through innovative software.

Julia Gleason is the Director of Product Management for Amazon Warehouse Distribution (AWD), where she leads the product, marketing, and UX for AWD's seller experiences. Julia has nearly 20 years of experience building technical products and leading cross-functional teams in a variety of industries, including retail (digital and physical) and operations for both internal and external customers. In her current role with AWD, Julia develops product, marketing, and technical strategies to create intuitive experiences that help sellers scale their businesses globally with Amazon's supply chain services. Julia lives in the Seattle area with her partner and two sons. Beyond work, she loves running, skiing, painting, and spending time with her family.

Jordan Greenberg is a Business Development Manager in the global logistics division of Amazon, based in New York City. For the past 4 years, Jordan has been a key part of the team responsible for expanding Amazon's worldwide delivery network and capabilities. In his current role, he works closely with cross-functional teams to analyze market trends, assess customer needs, and develop innovative solutions by leveraging data-driven insights to drive continuous improvements. Outside of work, Jordan enjoys gardening and is also an avid traveler, having visited dozens of countries around the world.

In 2022, Abel joined the Amazon Freight team to lead the Full Truck Load Inbound Account Management team. Since then, Abel and his team have helped enhance Amazon Freight’s capabilities by focusing on the customer’s needs and expectations. Putting the customer first has allowed for sustainable growth while creating an environment where the customer feels empowered to raise concerns and provide constructive feedback. Prior to Amazon, Abel served in the United States Marine Corps, retiring after 20 years.

Marcus Gverzdys leads global new business efforts at Perpetua, a software tool helping thousands of the world’s smartest brands and agencies grow on marketplaces through best in class performance tools, strategies and expertise. Prior to Pepretua, Marcus assumed a strategic role at Info-Tech Research Group guiding brands and government agencies through their enterprise application procurement process, working through the requirement gathering process to application selection.

DH Hill is a Senior Product Marketing Manager at Amazon Ads, leading a team responsible for the marketing of Amazon's ad solutions and creative technology offerings to businesses of all sizes and industries. With over a decade of experience in marketing and media, he possesses a deep understanding of the market dynamics and customer behavior that drive successful campaigns. His current passion is helping brands understand how retail media can be used to address a variety of marketing outcomes, including driving sales and building a brand.

As a Software Development Manager for Amazon's Retail Business Services, Venkatesh leads the team behind the award-winning Customer Anecdote Miner (CAM) and brand experience products. He holds a Master of Software Systems from the Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS) Pilani and a Post Graduate Program (PGP) in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning from the International Institute of Information Technology (IIIT) Bangalore. Since joining Amazon in 2021, he's focused on improving customer and brand experiences across the world in our store. With over 18 years of experience, Venkatesh develops strategies that increase sales, reducing returns, and drive meaningful growth for selling partners. He currently lives in Bangalore with his spouse and two daughters. A sports enthusiast, he excels in badminton and foosball.

Megan Iguchi is a Senior Product Manager for Amazon Returns and ReCommerce. In this role, Megan oversees products that enable Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA) sellers to better manage and recover value from customer-returned inventory. Since joining Amazon, Megan has led the strategy behind FBA Grade & Resell, FBA Returnless Resolutions, and participated in the creation of FBA Liquidations and Donations. She has over 13 years of experience building thoughtfully designed products for customers worldwide. Prior to Amazon, Megan taught Chemistry, Biology, and English as a Second Language (ESL) in Japan, Bolivia, Peru, and New York City. In her free time, she loves snowboarding and spending time with her husband, two kids, and dog.

As a Senior Product Manager at Amazon, Aakanksha Jain leads products and initiatives that focus on enhancing buyer and seller experiences for Fulfilled by Merchant (FBM) orders. With over eight years of experience in product management, she specializes in creating data-driven, user-friendly interfaces and has developed global tools for improving post-order experiences in the ecommerce fulfillment space. Before joining Amazon, Aakanksha worked for Wayfair and Comscore and holds a Master of Information Systems. Now residing in Austin, she enjoys an outdoorsy lifestyle, often exploring national parks and playing badminton.

As the Principal Product Leader for Seller Fulfilled Prime (SFP) at Amazon, Jenny Kim oversees strategic initiatives that focus on growing unique selection, increasing speed, and improving accuracy. Leaning on over 20 years of experience delivering high-impact solutions, Jenny is focused on creating meaningful experiences for selling partners and customers worldwide. Born in Hawaii and raised in Washington, Jenny will always say, "The West Coast is the best coast!"

Abhishek Kumar is the Senior Product Manager for Seller Growth and Development at Amazon. In his current role, Abhishek develops data-driven, personalized growth recommendation strategies that support selling partners in Amazon's store. Before joining Amazon, he managed a suite of products for a leading chip manufacturer and earned his MBA from Symbiosis International University. With over 10 years of experience in B2B and B2C settings across the retail, manufacturing, and life science industries, Abhishek has developed a keen perspective on launching thoughtfully designed digital products to users worldwide. Originally from India, he now lives in Phoenix with his wife, enjoys playing cricket, and loves listening to Bob Dylan and Bollywood music.

As the Head of Generative AI Image at Amazon Ads, Anita Lacea enables advertisers to create visually stunning ads with the click of a button. Anita pairs her broad expertise across the hardware and software industry with the latest innovations in generative AI to develop performant and cost-optimized solutions for selling partners, revolutionizing the way they connect with customers.

Kate LaChapelle is a Senior Technical Product Manager at Amazon with over 15 years of experience developing and launching ecommerce solutions. As a member of the Amazon Selling Partner Services organization for the past four years, she’s owned products that help brands grow their business in Amazon's store. Kate is passionate about providing sellers with the accurate and relevant data, insights, and tools they need to help them be successful. An Arizona native, she enjoys hiking and spending time with family.

Peter Larsen leads the Buy with Prime (BwP) and Multi-Channel Fulfillment (MCF) product lines. BwP enables sellers to offer free fast shipping to Prime members from their own DTC sites while MCF enables sellers to use Amazon's fulfillment infrastructure for their off-Amazon shipping. Previously, Peter was a VP in the Transportation Services, leading businesses including Amazon’s freight operation/technology. Peter started his Amazon career in Amazon Devices leading launches of the Kindle, Fire tablet and Fire TV product lines.

As the Head of Product at Veeqo, an Amazon company, Michelle Lau oversees product management. With over 10 years of experience working across different industries, Michelle is passionate about building software for small and medium-sized businesses that supports their growth. Michelle currently lives in Toronto with her husband and daughter.

Sylvio Lindenberg is a distinguished expert in omnichannel growth and a visionary leader in the retail industry. As the co-founder and CMO of Quartile, the world’s largest retail media optimization platform, he helps brands and sellers scale their businesses across various shopping platforms. With over 20 years in advertising, Lindenberg has a proven track record of maximizing digital presence for large CPG brands and private label sellers. He has held leadership roles at top advertising agencies, where he managed teams, developed strategies, and achieved impressive results. His expertise lies in optimizing Amazon advertising, expanding market reach, and driving revenue growth through award-winning cutting-edge AI and machine learning technologies.

David Liggins II, an Account Executive at Xmars, entrepreneur, mentor, and former Amazonian, has spent the last decade in ecommerce, not only building personal brands, but helping other SMB and Enterprise brands improve their position in an ever-growing online retail ecosystem. During this time, he has gained extensive knowledge on what it takes to succeed in a competitive marketplace environment and is keen on sharing his experiences to help other achieve their goals as well.

Jessie Liu is a Senior Technical Product Manager for Amazon Marketing Cloud (AMC), focusing on building solutions to help expand the reach and accessibility of AMC. Jessie initially joined Amazon as an analytics and media manager, where she provided consultative advisory on the advertising strategy using AMC and Amazon first party signals. Since then, she has developed research and analytics studies on retail, media and, consumer insights across Amazon's advertising products. With over 10 years of experience in digital and advertising analytics, Jessie has driven meaningful change for sellers worldwide through her innovative approaches to advertising and measurement. She lives in New York City with her husband and two daughters. Outside of work, she loves visiting museums and hiking in Prospect Park with her family.

Andrea Marquez is the Host and Senior Producer of Amazon's award-winning podcast, This is Small Business. With over 10 years of storytelling and production experience, she joined Amazon to provide resources to aspiring entrepreneurs and small business owners while sharing inspiring stories of Amazon sellers. Named one of the Nation's Hispanic 30 Under 30 Leaders for empowering the Latinx community, Andrea is also the creator and former host of an award-winning bilingual podcast. She holds an M.A. from Harvard and a B.A. from Columbia.

Shea McNichol is a Senior Product Marketing Manager at Amazon, specializing in helping selling partners successfully launch new products. With over a decade of experience in product management, brand management, customer relationship management, loyalty, and personalized marketing, she is dedicated to creating solutions that empower selling partners across the world to introduce new selection and build brands that delight customers. Based in Phoenix, Shea enjoys spending time with her family, exploring the outdoors (weather permitting), and horseback riding.

Dharmesh joined Amazon in 2013. He currently leads WW Selling Partner Services, whose mission is to enable the long-term success of our selling partners by providing the most trusted shopping and selling experience and by providing powerful solutions for accelerating our selling partners’ business growth. Prior to Amazon, Dharmesh worked at Microsoft, his own startup, and Bain & Company, and he has multiple degrees from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and Harvard Business School. Dharmesh enjoys spending time with family and friends, and travelling to new places around the world.

Niraj Mehta is a Senior Product Manager at Amazon, overseeing customer relationship management (CRM) strategy for brands. With over nine years of experience, he's passionate about building scalable tools that help brands grow their business and customer lifetime value. Prior to joining Amazon, Niraj worked at Uber, where he focused on building products for driver partners. Niraj recently moved from India to Seattle and loves exploring the mountains and lakes with his wife.

As a Senior Sales Account Executive at Veeqo, an Amazon company, Ross Miller oversees the execution of business development strategies and merchant adoption. Joining Amazon shortly after graduating from college, Ross has over 12 years of experience helping scale sales teams while supporting Amazon selling partners across programs like Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA), Seller Growth, and now Veeqo. In addition to his ecommerce and logistics industry expertise, Ross is a selling partner in Amazon's store himself. Originally from Washington, he now resides in Austin, Texas with his wife and three children. Outside of work, Miller enjoys golfing and exploring new weekend escapes with his young family.

Dave Nadel is a director of Selling Partner Experience at Amazon, overseeing many of the tools sellers use daily to manage and grow their business. Dave has been at Amazon for over 10 years, and has spent most of that time as a product and engineering leader building new experiences to drive growth for Amazon sellers across the globe. Today, Dave’s team builds cross cutting solutions that power a suite of powerful yet simple tools designed to help sellers accelerate their success. Prior to Amazon, Dave worked in digital advertising, where he helped small and medium service providers across the country build brand awareness and acquire new customers.

Kayvon Nazarian is the CEO of ZonPrep, focusing on scaling their extensive FBA Prep 3PL operation for enterprise brands in improving the Inbound to FBA process. Prior to ZonPrep, Kayvon was Co-Founded a $10M+ Amazon Exclusive brand, which he capitalized on such as an opportunity to develop tools, systems, strategies and an operation to support high volume FBA Prep for brands beyond his own. Kayvon’s ability to think as a fellow brand owner, his obsession for improvement and win-win mutual growth, uniquely drives efficiency and cost reduction for sellers daily.

As a Sales Lead at Amazon, Jessica Newcomb manages a team of account executives that support selling partners using Fulfilled by Merchant (FBM) and Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA). From selling partners just beginning their journey in our store to those that have been selling for years, Jessica's team offers fulfillment and logistics expertise to a wide range of businesses. A graduate of the University of Florida and the University of Georgia—go Dawgs!—Jessica brings over 20 years of business development experience to Amazon. She currently lives in Arlington, working from Amazon's HQ2.

Jeff Nickerson is a Senior Manager of Brand Experience and Excellence at Amazon. His mission is to empower selling partners to thrive and grow a differentiated business that customers love and trust in Amazon's store. Prior to his work with brands, Jeff launched the Seller Fulfilled Prime (SFP) program. He currently resides in Seattle with his wife and two daughters.

Claire is focused on ensuring bad actors are unable to operate in Amazon’s store or commit fraud and abuse through selling accounts, as well as the seller experience for Account Health, including Account Health Dashboard (AHD), Rating (AHR) and Assurance (AHA), and seller account compliance. She has worked at Amazon for over 14 years and in the seller business for 6 years in a number of different roles, formerly leading programs such as small business empowerment, seller communities and Strategic Account Services. She lives in Seattle with her family.

Rohan Oommen joined Amazon in 2015 and is the VP of Worldwide Trustworthy Shopping Experience (TSE). TSE’s mission is to guarantee a trustworthy and worry-free shopping experience on Amazon, so our customers can shop with confidence, and in turn enable the long-term success of our selling partners. Rohan has spent 25+ years building innovative products and services. Prior to joining Amazon, he worked in Microsoft’s Xbox business for 14 years, US and UK, and at Nestlé India for 3 years prior to that. He holds an MBA from Kellogg School of Management, Northwestern University.

Priya Padmanabhan is the Vice President of Worldwide Selling Partner Infrastructure and Financial Services at Amazon. With over 20‐ years of experience as a technology, product and business executive, she now leads an organization that enables the long‐term success of Amazon's selling partners by providing scalable and flexible cross‐cutting technology frameworks and financial services. These technologies empower internal and external builders to innovate on behalf of our selling partners and drive the business through accurate and timely decision‐making at scale. Priya currently lives in the greater Seattle area with her husband and three sons.

Robin Paris is a Senior Manager at Amazon Ads, leading the global marketing team that's focused on helping small and medium-sized businesses grow in Amazon's store. After earning her bachelor's degree from the University of Washington, Robin began her career in sales and marketing, joining Amazon in 2017. Initially spearheading Fire TV demand programs, Robin transitioned to Amazon Ads in 2021. With over 15 years of marketing experience, Robin’s passion lies in developing data-driven marketing strategies that improve the customer experience. When not leveraging her expertise at Amazon, Robin resides in Seattle with her husband and 4-year-old daughter.

Jason Patrao is the Director of Engineering for Prime Air. He is responsible for all aspects of drone development including hardware, software & autonomy, as well as the mission planning & orchestration systems. Before joining Prime Air, he held leadership roles in Amazon’s autonomous sidewalk delivery robot & retail experience programs. Prior to Amazon, he was an engineer at Microsoft working on high performance distributed software systems. He received his undergraduate in Computer Engineering from the University of Mumbai & Master’s degree in computer science from Texas A&M University.

As a Senior Technical Product Manager at Amazon, Egon Pedrazzini oversees product strategy for Brand Registry. Specifically, Egon focuses on Brand Registry Foundation and Experience, owning the product and technology supporting enrollment, roles, ASIN association with brands, and engagement experiences. Joining the company nearly 12 years ago, Egon began his time at Amazon in a finance role before transitioning into product. Originally from Switzerland, he now lives in Seattle with his wife and son. Outside of work, he enjoys playing futball ("soccer") and cooking.

As the Head of Marketing for Amazon Lending, Ilham Perdana leads a team that focuses on helping small and medium businesses learn about ways to finance their goals. Ilham began his career with Amazon in 2008, serving in multiple roles across retail, vendor, and account management before moving into marketing and leading teams in the US and Japan over the last decade. A graduate of University of Washington, Ilham enjoys being with his family and spending time on his various hobbies—tinkering in vintage watches and getting his hands wet with marine aquariums.

Gopal is the VP of Amazon's World Wide Returns and ReCommerce teams. Previously, he led the Amazon Distribution and Fulfillment Solutions business, including building a Warehouse Management System product to effectively manage distribution centers, and managing an eCommerce fulfillment business that helps organizations reach their consumers seamlessly for their DTC channels. He spent 5 years in as part of the founding team building the marketplace business in India. Gopal has an MBA from Kellogg School of Management and a BS in Computer Science and Engineering from University of Madras, India.

Apoorva Prasad leads Global Logistics for Amazon, which encompasses global import & export logistics, and domestic transportation. This team’s mission is to enable the success of our selling partners by providing powerful supply chain solutions that quickly and reliably move products from manufacturing locations to customers around the world. Apoorva, a 13+ year Amazonian with diverse experience delivering bar-raising customer experiences, started her career as a seasonal hire in Operations, and has fond memories of helping solve seller problems on the front-line team in her very first job!

Ilene Rafii is a Principal Product Manager leading the Brand Technology team for Fashion Fit, overseeing tooling to improve the fit experience for brands, selling partners, and internal customers. After earning her MBA from Harvard Business School, Ilene initially joined Amazon as a Product Manager where she led the Customer Experience (CX) product team at Amazon Style. In her free time, Ilene enjoys staying outdoors and gardening.

Joyce Rallanka is a Director at Amazon, leading the Strategic Account Services (SAS) program for sellers. With a 20-year track record of delivering growth in both the business-to-consumer (B2C) and business-to-business (B2B) space, Joyce is a change agent who drives positive impact at scale. After a career in brand management at Procter & Gamble, Joyce joined Amazon in 2015 and has held various leadership positions developing brands, programs, categories, and large organizations across consumer product goods, private brands, and ecommerce retail. Today, Joyce leads a team that oversees high-touch relationships with thousands of sellers in the Amazon store. Joyce also mentors many different Amazonians, leads DEI efforts within her organization, and is an Amazon Bar Raiser. Originally from South Jersey, she has made her way west through South Bend, Indiana (Go Irish!) and Cincinnati, now residing in Seattle with her husband, son, daughter, and pet snake.

As a Tech Business Developer with Buy with Prime, Matt Reilly specializes in helping brands increase traffic and visibility to their site. Before joining Amazon in 2022, Matt was an ecommerce strategist at Google and managed accounts at Gartner. He holds a Bachelor of Business Administration in Supply Chain Management and Information Systems from the University of Pittsburgh.

Giorgio Riboldi is a Senior Risk Manager for EU Regulatory Compliance at Amazon, managing the implementation of compliance programs like the General Product Safety Regulation. Giorgio has been part of the compliance team since 2016 and has overseen complex programs like product safety, recalls, and regulatory framework in the EU. With over 10 years of experience, Giorgio is committed to helping improve the selling partner experience in Amazon's store while ensuring products comply with applicable regulations. Originally from Italy, he now lives in Luxembourg with his wife and daughter, and enjoys playing basketball and table tennis.

Jay Richman is the Vice President of Creative Experiences, overseeing all creative formats, builders, and performance across Sponsored Ads and Amazon DSP including areas such as AI-Generated Creative and Interactive TV Formats. Prior to Amazon, Jay was the Vice President of Monetization at Spotify. He built Spotify's early subscription, advertising, and creator businesses, before taking on the role of Advertising GM. He played a pivotal role in guiding the company through its IPO, driving global expansion and significant growth, while broadening its mission from music to include products and audiobooks.

As a Senior Product Manager with Amazon's Seller Fulfilled Services, Olga Rousey researches selling partner perspectives about new and existing products for Fulfillment by Merchant (FBM). Olga earned her MBA from Emory and has over 15 years of experience working in supply chain, freight research, and benchmarking at Amazon, Dat.com, and consulting firms. Originally from Russia, Olga has a diverse international background, as she's lived in four countries and fluently speaks four languages. Olga currently resides in Atlanta with her husband, three kids, and cat.

Jasleen Sachdeva is a seasoned Senior Product Manager specializing in Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA) supply chain strategy for Amazon extra-large (AMXL) items. Jasleen joined Amazon after earning her Masters in Supply Chain Engineering from Georgia Tech, serving in multiple different roles across our supply chain. Her expertise lies in working backwards from selling partner feedback to launch new products and initiatives that streamline their supply chain experience. Outside of work, Jasleen loves singing and being out in the nature with her sweet goldendoodle, Elina.

Rebecca Salt is a Director of Amazon Freight and Amazon Shipping, overseeing the strategy for each business’ marketing program. With an array of experience in branding, communications, and messaging, her team tells the story behind Amazon Freight and how it delivers for both selling partners and shippers. Similarly, Rebecca drives awareness for Amazon Shipping—our fast and reliable parcel service—and manages the in-house creative engine for Amazon’s transportation brands. With over 25 years of experience in the transportation industry, Rebecca has worked for Exel Logistics, DHL, and CEVA Logistics, among others. She lives in Seattle with her husband, daughter, and two dogs.

As a Senior Business Developer with Growth Education Services at Amazon, Jennifer Sarullo optimizes strategies across categories to drive new product selection and help selling partners secure first sales. She has conducted extensive research on the factors that influence the cold start problem and works to scale processes that boost top-line growth. Prior to joining Amazon in 2021 as a senior customer success manager in Strategic Account Services (SAS), Jennifer spent over 15 years working in business development and merchandising in the fashion industry. A New York native, she enjoys traveling, yoga, and playing soccer with her son.

Katie Scott is the Director of Selling Partner Communities at Amazon, focused on building lasting connections with and among our sellers.
